Problem Statement:

The current process for automatically creating regional segments is inefficient and prone to delays. It relies on calculated fields as a trigger and initial step for staging data. This approach introduces latency and potential inconsistencies, impacting the timeliness and accuracy of regional segment updates.

Technical Solution:

To address the inefficiency, we will implement the following solution:

Generate Active Line of Business Report:

Create a scheduled report that retrieves all active Line of Business data.
This report will include the Line of Business name, associated country, and segment information.
The report will be generated in XML format for structured data processing.
XSLT Transformation:

Develop an XSLT transformation to process the generated XML report.
The XSLT will extract the unique combinations of region and segment from the Line of Business data.
This step will consolidate the data and eliminate redundancies.
Regional Segment Creation Logic:

Implement a system process that consumes the transformed data from the XSLT.
The system will compare the extracted region/segment combinations with existing regional segments.
For any missing regional segments, the system will create new entries using a "create-only" rule.
This ensures that existing regional segments are not unintentionally updated or overwritten.
This will prevent issues that could arise from a create/update action, such as data loss.
